.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_BaseHighlighter
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Base Highlighter is an abstract class that all other highlighters inherit and are required to implement the public methods.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: As this is an abstract class, it cannot be applied directly to a game object and performs no logic.

methods.name: GetActiveHighlighter(GameObject obj)
methods.summary: The GetActiveHighlighter method checks the given game object for a valid and active highlighter.

params.value: The game object to check for a highlighter on.

methods.name: GetOption<T>(Dictionary<string, object> options, string key)
methods.summary: The GetOption method is used to return a value from the options array if the given key exists.
methods.returns: The value in the options at the given key returned in the provided system type.

params.value: The dictionary of options to check in.
The system type that is expected to be returned.

methods.syntax: public virtual T GetOption<T>(Dictionary<string, object> options, string key)
methods.linkedSyntax: public virtual T GetOption<T>(Dictionary<string, object> options, string key)

methods.name: Highlight(Nullable<Color> color, float duration)
methods.summary: The Highlight method is used to initiate the highlighting logic to apply to an object.

params.value: An optional colour to highlight the game object to. The highlight colour may already have been set in the Initialise method so may not be required here.
An optional duration of how long before the highlight has occured. It can be used by highlighters to fade the colour if possible.

methods.syntax: public abstract void Highlight(Nullable<Color> color, float duration)
methods.linkedSyntax: public abstract void Highlight(Nullable<Color> color, float duration)

methods.name: Initialise(Nullable<Color> color, Dictionary<string, object> options)
methods.summary: The Initalise method is used to set up the state of the highlighter.

params.value: An optional colour may be passed through at point of initialisation in case the highlighter requires it.
An optional dictionary of highlighter specific options that may be differ with highlighter implementations.

methods.syntax: public abstract void Initialise(Nullable<Color> color, Dictionary<string, object> options)
methods.linkedSyntax: public abstract void Initialise(Nullable<Color> color, Dictionary<string, object> options)

methods.name: ResetHighlighter()
methods.summary: The ResetHighlighter method is used to reset the highlighter if anything on the object has changed. It should be called by any scripts changing object materials or colours.

methods.name: Unhighlight(Nullable<Color> color, float duration)
methods.summary: The Unhighlight method is used to initiate the logic that returns an object back to it's original appearance.

params.value: An optional colour that could be used during the unhighlight phase. Usually will be left as null.
An optional duration of how long before the unhighlight has occured.

methods.syntax: public abstract void Unhighlight(Nullable<Color> color, float duration)
methods.linkedSyntax: public abstract void Unhighlight(Nullable<Color> color, float duration)

methods.name: UsesClonedObject()
methods.summary: The UsesClonedObject method is used to return whether the current highlighter creates a cloned object to do the highlighting with.
methods.returns: Returns true if the highlighter creates a cloned object to apply the highlighter on, returns false if no additional object is created.
